46:03.381 --> 46:05.176
- You mean an institution?

46:05.176 --> 46:09.318
- She's leaning in physically
to the conversation,

46:09.318 --> 46:11.216
kind of trying to
figure this guy out.

46:11.216 --> 46:12.873
And I think, it feels
like what she's trying

46:12.873 --> 46:14.116
to figure out is,

46:14.116 --> 46:14.806
why is this guy not
trying to fuck me?

46:14.806 --> 46:15.980
[creepy music]

46:15.980 --> 46:17.567
- We all go a little
mad sometimes.

46:20.985 --> 46:21.813
Haven't you?

46:22.780 --> 46:25.196
- When you watch
Hitchcock films,

46:25.196 --> 46:27.336
sexuality is something

46:27.336 --> 46:30.788
that comes up for the lead
characters almost always.

46:30.788 --> 46:33.238
Like sometimes, it's a
little bit more subtextual,

46:33.238 --> 46:34.722
but with something
like "Psycho,"

46:34.722 --> 46:38.761
it feels like he is really
inviting the audience

46:38.761 --> 46:43.766
to look at a particular
part of life, i.e. sex,

46:45.181 --> 46:49.530
and how that's connected to
morals, ethics, identity,

46:50.669 --> 46:52.050
anything else that
you hold dear.

46:52.050 --> 46:54.812
[tense music]

46:54.812 --> 46:57.780
- Hitchcock's legacy and
filmography are complicated.

46:57.780 --> 47:00.818
He's had some really
interesting women characters,

47:00.818 --> 47:04.407
but he also famously said that
we should torture the women

47:04.407 --> 47:06.340
to create good entertainment.

47:06.340 --> 47:09.205
[rain splattering]

47:09.205 --> 47:12.105
- It makes sense that
some of the characters

47:12.105 --> 47:13.382
that we villainize

47:13.382 --> 47:16.937
in horror movies are the
products of suppression.

47:18.387 --> 47:21.942
If you are treated as a
pathology, as a sickness,

47:21.942 --> 47:23.841
then sickness is
what you become.

47:24.842 --> 47:26.464
[tense music]

47:26.464 --> 47:28.535
- [Michael] When I
see Anthony Perkins

47:28.535 --> 47:30.537
in a movie like "Psycho,"

47:30.537 --> 47:32.435
- I've caused you some trouble.

47:32.435 --> 47:33.264
- No.

47:34.265 --> 47:36.508
Mother, my mother,

47:37.509 --> 47:38.407
what is a phrase?

47:40.236 --> 47:42.929
She isn't quite herself today.

47:42.929 --> 47:47.726
- The character
of Norman Bates is

47:47.726 --> 47:49.936
a queer man playing a queer man.

47:49.936 --> 47:51.627
- [Norman] Please, mother.

47:51.627 --> 47:54.906
- [Mother] No, I will not
hide in the fruit cellar.

47:54.906 --> 47:56.597
You think I'm fruity, huh?

47:56.597 --> 47:58.737
- There's a different
kind of connection

47:58.737 --> 48:00.774
between a mother and her gay son

48:00.774 --> 48:03.570
and you really see
Hitchcock kind of exploiting

48:03.570 --> 48:04.812
that in "Psycho"

48:05.986 --> 48:07.746
without really having to
say much else about him.

48:07.746 --> 48:10.922
We all kind of pick up
on, "Oh, that's why."

48:12.130 --> 48:14.892
- Well, a a boy's best
friend is his mother.

48:14.892 --> 48:17.549
- That was, in
Hitchcock's design,

48:17.549 --> 48:20.587
essential that Norman be my dad.

48:20.587 --> 48:23.176
[bright music]

48:32.392 --> 48:33.427
- Are you alone?

48:33.427 --> 48:36.223
[bright music]

48:36.223 --> 48:40.193
♪ I've got a date with the
prettiest girl in school ♪

48:40.193 --> 48:42.574
- It was very
comfortable for my father

48:42.574 --> 48:46.509
to be an All
American straight kid

48:46.509 --> 48:49.305
who could headline movies
in, and movie musicals.

48:49.305 --> 48:50.237
That was easy.

48:50.237 --> 48:52.377
- I don't want to die.

48:52.377 --> 48:55.001
I don't know if I could
kill anyone if I tried.

48:55.001 --> 48:57.658
- He was a young,
teenage heart throb.

48:57.658 --> 48:59.453
He was always kind
of a little off

48:59.453 --> 49:01.697
and that was what made
people interested, I think.

49:01.697 --> 49:03.941
- And you're killing me. You've
been killing me for years.

49:03.941 --> 49:05.563
Yes, you have,
and it's too much.

49:05.563 --> 49:08.704
- He went to acting as a way
to be anything but himself.

49:08.704 --> 49:11.120
- You are like all the
beautiful things in this wood.

49:11.120 --> 49:12.984
- He was tender and warm

49:12.984 --> 49:14.434
and everybody wanted
to take him home.

49:14.434 --> 49:15.953
And then he did "Psycho."

49:17.333 --> 49:19.715
Norman Bates changed Anthony
Perkins' life forever.

49:19.715 --> 49:21.751
- Gee, I'm sorry I didn't
hear you in all this rain.

49:21.751 --> 49:25.514
- "Psycho" appears, and
it's like there's no mask.

49:25.514 --> 49:28.896
You're playing your
own internal stuff.

49:28.896 --> 49:30.346
There's no remove.

49:30.346 --> 49:31.830
- Did she arrive with anyone?

49:32.762 --> 49:33.971
- No.

49:33.971 --> 49:36.076
- Did you spend
the night with her?

49:36.076 --> 49:37.284
- No.

49:37.284 --> 49:38.976
- He is giving
you that character

49:38.976 --> 49:43.981
in every twitch and in every
nervous, jittery, candy eating,

49:44.878 --> 49:46.155
you know, thing that he's doing.

49:46.155 --> 49:49.365
Hitchcock is cannily,
and maybe cruelly,

49:49.365 --> 49:51.712
finding all the
Anthony Perkins parts

49:51.712 --> 49:53.991
of Norman Bates and vice versa.

49:53.991 --> 49:56.924
That just becomes a thing
that you just don't shake.

49:58.064 --> 50:01.101
- The fact that, yet
again, in his career,

50:01.101 --> 50:06.106
Hitchcock cast a
closeted gay actor

50:07.245 --> 50:09.937
to play the monster male
figure in his movie,

50:09.937 --> 50:11.284
I think is telling.

50:11.284 --> 50:13.838
It was clearly a
pattern in his career.

50:13.838 --> 50:15.633
[water bubbling]

50:15.633 --> 50:18.325
- Hitchcock knew that my
father was queer and it,

50:18.325 --> 50:22.916
that was sort of a motivator
in hiring him for the part.

50:22.916 --> 50:26.023
Hitchcock was too
much of a trickster

50:26.023 --> 50:31.028
and a little imp to not want
to add that really vital edge.

50:33.064 --> 50:34.307
- Wife's taking a nap,

50:34.307 --> 50:36.240
and I never can keep
quiet enough for her,

50:36.240 --> 50:39.070
so, I just thought I'd
look you up and talk.

50:39.070 --> 50:41.452
- The John Gavin scenes,
for me, with my dad are,

50:41.452 --> 50:45.490
it's like my dad against
