50:45.490 --> 50:46.733
- You look frightened.

50:46.733 --> 50:48.045
Have I been saying
something frightening?

50:48.045 --> 50:49.563
- I don't know what
you've been saying.

50:49.563 --> 50:51.427
- Hitchcock was
probably impish enough

50:51.427 --> 50:53.740
to kind of really lean into that

50:53.740 --> 50:56.950
and hire Gavin to
mop the floor with.

50:56.950 --> 50:59.056
Norman couldn't
possibly stop him.

50:59.056 --> 51:01.230
[menacing music]

51:01.230 --> 51:04.544
And of course, he's wrong.

51:06.304 --> 51:10.584
- He imbues Norman Bates
with colors and flavors

51:10.584 --> 51:13.277
that are above and beyond
what's there on the page,

51:13.277 --> 51:14.830
that I as a gay man who,

51:14.830 --> 51:16.625
you know, spent some, at least,

51:16.625 --> 51:18.696
thankfully not my whole
life, but you know,

51:18.696 --> 51:21.078
some of my adolescence
certainly in the closet,

51:22.217 --> 51:23.735
can really relate to.

51:23.735 --> 51:25.530
I was a mama's
boy too. You know?

51:26.738 --> 51:28.775
- Sometimes, when she
talks to me like that,

51:29.983 --> 51:32.779
I feel I'd like to go
up there and curse her

51:32.779 --> 51:36.231
and leave her forever
or at least a fire.

51:41.443 --> 51:43.134
But I know I can't.

51:43.134 --> 51:45.723
- Anthony Perkins is
really channeling the pain

51:45.723 --> 51:48.105
of not being able to
express his queerness.

51:48.105 --> 51:50.210
And that's why we remember it

51:50.210 --> 51:52.281
as such a powerhouse performance

51:52.281 --> 51:54.939
because it really is
somebody's real lived pain.

51:54.939 --> 51:56.975
- So, the narrative,
in my house,

51:56.975 --> 51:59.633
was "Psycho" had been
too right for my dad

51:59.633 --> 52:03.292
and therefore, was the end
of him as an actor, really.

52:03.292 --> 52:05.915
It was like his coming out and
his funeral at the same time.

52:05.915 --> 52:07.848
In one swift move, the whole,

52:07.848 --> 52:11.093
the whole jig was up.

52:12.129 --> 52:13.992
"Psycho" was no good for him.

52:13.992 --> 52:15.235
It was too good,

52:15.235 --> 52:17.686
it was too good, and
therefore, no good.

52:17.686 --> 52:19.170
It had damaged my
father's career

52:19.170 --> 52:23.347
because now no one could
see him as anything else.

52:23.347 --> 52:26.971
There was no freedom in 1960
to say, "Oh, and by the way,

52:26.971 --> 52:29.180
the reason why I'm so
great in this role,

52:29.180 --> 52:30.906
I'm just like that."

52:32.183 --> 52:34.358
